        TargetCollectionResource createTargetCollectionResource(String url)
        Creates a new target collection resource from the passed url. It will be loaded when it is used to create a Tracker.
        Parameters:
        url - Url to the resource file. This can be a http url, a local file(file://) or an asset (file:///android_asset()
        Returns:
        The newly created TargetCollectionResource instance

      • createTargetCollectionResource

        @Deprecated
TargetCollectionResource createTargetCollectionResource(String url,
                                                                    TargetCollectionResourceLoadingCallback loadingCallback)
        Deprecated. Use createTargetCollectionResource(String) and TargetCollectionResource.load(com.wikitude.tracker.TargetCollectionResourceLoadingCallback) instead.
        Creates a new target collection resource from the passed url and loads it immediately.
        Parameters:
        url - url Url to the resource file. This can be a http url, a local file(file://) or an asset (file:///android_asset()
        loadingCallback - Callback object that is notified when the loading succeeds of fails
        Returns:
        The newly created TargetCollectionResource instance

      • createCloudRecognitionService

        @Deprecated
CloudRecognitionService createCloudRecognitionService(String clientToken,
                                                                  String targetCollectionId,
                                                                  CloudRecognitionServiceInitializationCallback initializationCallback,
                                                                  CloudRecognitionServiceConfiguration configuration)
        Deprecated. Use createCloudRecognitionService(String, String, String, CloudRecognitionServiceInitializationCallback, CloudRecognitionServiceConfiguration) instead.
        Creates a new CloudRecognitionService with the passed authentication details
        Parameters:
        clientToken - Your client token
        targetCollectionId - The collection id of the target collection that should be loaded
        initializationCallback - CloudRecognitionServiceInitializationCallback object that is notified when the initialization succeeds or fails.
        configuration - CloudRecognitionServiceConfiguration object that defines how the CloudRecognitionService behaves.
        Returns:
        The newly created CloudRecognitionService instance
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If clientToken or targetCollectionId are null.

      • createCloudRecognitionService

                                                      String groupId,

                                                      CloudRecognitionServiceInitializationCallback initializationCallback,
                                                      CloudRecognitionServiceConfiguration configuration)
        Creates a new CloudRecognitionService with the passed authentication details
        Parameters:
        clientToken - Your client token
        groupId - Your group id
        targetCollectionId - The collection id of the target collection that should be loaded
        initializationCallback - CloudRecognitionServiceInitializationCallback object that is notified when the initialization succeeds or fails.
        configuration - CloudRecognitionServiceConfiguration object that defines how the CloudRecognitionService behaves.
        Returns:
        The newly created CloudRecognitionService instance
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If clientToken or targetCollectionId are null.

      • destroyTargetCollectionResource

        void destroyTargetCollectionResource(TargetCollectionResource targetCollectionResource)
        Destroys a TargetCollectionResource. A TargetCollectionResource should not be destroyed until the ImageTrackers or ObjectTrackers that are using it are also destroyed.
        Parameters:
        targetCollectionResource - The TargetCollectionResource instance that should be destroyed
